<body>
Reports derived tables without aliases.
<p>Example (MySQL):</p>
<pre><code>CREATE TABLE table1 (id INT, name VARCHAR(20), cats FLOAT);
CREATE TABLE table2 (id INT, age INTEGER);

SELECT id AS ID, name, cats, age
FROM (SELECT table1.id, name, cats, age
FROM table1
JOIN table2 ON table1.id = table2.id);</code></pre>
<p>According to <a href="https://dev.mysql.com/doc/refman/8.0/en/derived-tables.html">Derived Tables at dev.mysql.com</a>, an alias is
  mandatory. You can add the alias by using the <b>Introduce alias</b> quick-fix.</p>
<p>After the quick-fix is applied:</p>
<pre><code>SELECT id AS ID, name, cats, age
FROM (SELECT table1.id, name, cats, age
FROM table1
JOIN table2 ON table1.id = table2.id);</code></pre>
